31void testPinRegisters()
32{
33 auto go = [&] (bool pin) {
34 Procedure proc;
35 RegisterSet csrs;
36 csrs.merge(RegisterSet::calleeSaveRegisters());
37 csrs.exclude(RegisterSet::stackRegisters());
38 if (pin) {
39 csrs.forEach(
40 [&] (Reg reg) {
41 proc.pinRegister(reg);
42 });
43 }
44 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
45 Value* a = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
46 Value* b = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
47 Value* c = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR2);
48 Value* d = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::regCS0);
49 root->appendNew<CCallValue>(
50 proc, Void, Origin(),
51 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), static_cast<intptr_t>(0x1234)));
52 root->appendNew<CCallValue>(
53 proc, Void, Origin(),
54 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), static_cast<intptr_t>(0x1235)),
55 a, b, c);
56 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
57 patchpoint->appendSomeRegister(d);
58 unsigned optLevel = proc.optLevel();
59 patchpoint->setGenerator(
60 [&] (CCallHelpers&, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
61 if (optLevel > 1)
62 CHECK_EQ(params[0].gpr(), GPRInfo::regCS0);
63 });
64 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin());
65 auto code = compileProc(proc);
66 bool usesCSRs = false;
67 for (Air::BasicBlock* block : proc.code()) {
68 for (Air::Inst& inst : *block) {
69 if (inst.kind.opcode == Air::Patch && inst.origin == patchpoint)
70 continue;
71 inst.forEachTmpFast(
72 [&] (Air::Tmp tmp) {
73 if (tmp.isReg())
74 usesCSRs |= csrs.get(tmp.reg());
75 });
76 }
77 }
78 if (proc.optLevel() < 2) {
79 // Our less good register allocators may use the
80 // pinned CSRs in a move.
81 usesCSRs = false;
82 }
83 for (const RegisterAtOffset& regAtOffset : proc.calleeSaveRegisterAtOffsetList())
84 usesCSRs |= csrs.get(regAtOffset.reg());
85 CHECK_EQ(usesCSRs, !pin);
86 };
87
88 go(true);
89 go(false);
90}

92void testX86LeaAddAddShlLeft()
93{
94 // Add(Add(Shl(@x, $c), @y), $d)
95 Procedure proc;
96 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
97 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(
98 proc, Add, Origin(),
99 root->appendNew<Value>(
100 proc, Add, Origin(),
101 root->appendNew<Value>(
102 proc, Shl, Origin(),
103 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1),
104 root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 2)),
105 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0)),
106 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 100));
107 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), result);
108
109 auto code = compileProc(proc);
110 if (proc.optLevel() > 1)
111 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "lea 0x64(%rdi,%rsi,4), %rax");
112 else
113 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "lea");
114 CHECK_EQ(invoke<intptr_t>(*code, 1, 2), (1 + (2 << 2)) + 100);
115}

142void testX86LeaAddAdd()
143{
144 // Add(Add(@x, @y), $c)
145 Procedure proc;

147 Value* result = root->appendNew<Value>(
148 proc, Add, Origin(),

153 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 100));
154 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), result);

160 *code,
161 [&] (const char* disassembly) -> bool {
162 return strstr(disassembly, "lea 0x64(%rdi,%rsi), %rax")
163 || strstr(disassembly, "lea 0x64(%rsi,%rdi), %rax");
164 },
165 "Expected to find something like lea 0x64(%rdi,%rsi), %rax but didn't!");
166 }

338void testReduceStrengthReassociation(bool flip)
339{
340 // Add(Add(@x, $c), @y) -> Add(Add(@x, @y), $c)
341 // and
342 // Add(@y, Add(@x, $c)) -> Add(Add(@x, @y), $c)
343 Procedure proc;
344 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
345 Value* arg1 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
346 Value* arg2 = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
347
348 Value* innerAdd = root->appendNew<Value>(
349 proc, Add, Origin(), arg1,
350 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 42));
351
352 Value* outerAdd;
353 if (flip)
354 outerAdd = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), arg2, innerAdd);
355 else
356 outerAdd = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), innerAdd, arg2);
357
358 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), outerAdd);
359
360 proc.resetReachability();
361
362 if (shouldBeVerbose()) {
363 dataLog("IR before reduceStrength:\n");
364 dataLog(proc);
365 }
366
367 reduceStrength(proc);
368
369 if (shouldBeVerbose()) {
370 dataLog("IR after reduceStrength:\n");
371 dataLog(proc);
372 }
373
374 CHECK_EQ(root->last()->opcode(), Return);
375 CHECK_EQ(root->last()->child(0)->opcode(), Add);
376 CHECK(root->last()->child(0)->child(1)->isIntPtr(42));
377 CHECK_EQ(root->last()->child(0)->child(0)->opcode(), Add);
378 CHECK(
379 (root->last()->child(0)->child(0)->child(0) == arg1 && root->last()->child(0)->child(0)->child(1) == arg2) ||
380 (root->last()->child(0)->child(0)->child(0) == arg2 && root->last()->child(0)->child(0)->child(1) == arg1));
381}

383void testLoadBaseIndexShift2()
384{
385 Procedure proc;
386 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
387 root->appendNew<Value>(
388 proc, Return, Origin(),
389 root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
390 proc, Load, Int32, Origin(),
391 root->appendNew<Value>(
392 proc, Add, Origin(),
393 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0),
394 root->appendNew<Value>(
395 proc, Shl, Origin(),
396 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1),
397 root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 2)))));
398 auto code = compileProc(proc);
399 if (isX86() && proc.optLevel() > 1)
400 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "(%rdi,%rsi,4)");
401 int32_t value = 12341234;
402 char* ptr = bitwise_cast<char*>(&value);
403 for (unsigned i = 0; i < 10; ++i)
404 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int32_t>(*code, ptr - (static_cast<intptr_t>(1) << static_cast<intptr_t>(2)) * i, i), 12341234);
405}

431void testOptimizeMaterialization()
432{
433 Procedure proc;
434 if (proc.optLevel() < 2)
435 return;
436
437 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
438 root->appendNew<CCallValue>(
439 proc, Void, Origin(),
440 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 0x123423453456llu),
441 root->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), 0x123423453456llu + 35));
442 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin());
443
444 auto code = compileProc(proc);
445 bool found = false;
446 for (Air::BasicBlock* block : proc.code()) {
447 for (Air::Inst& inst : *block) {
448 if (inst.kind.opcode != Air::Add64)
449 continue;
450 if (inst.args[0] != Air::Arg::imm(35))
451 continue;
452 found = true;
453 }
454 }
455 CHECK(found);
456}

458template<typename Func>
459void generateLoop(Procedure& proc, const Func& func)
460{
461 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
462 BasicBlock* loop = proc.addBlock();
463 BasicBlock* end = proc.addBlock();
464
465 UpsilonValue* initialIndex = root->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(
466 proc, Origin(), root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 0));
467 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Jump, Origin());
468 root->setSuccessors(loop);
469
470 Value* index = loop->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Int32, Origin());
471 initialIndex->setPhi(index);
472
473 Value* one = func(loop, index);
474
475 Value* nextIndex = loop->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), index, one);
476 UpsilonValue* loopIndex = loop->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), nextIndex);
477 loopIndex->setPhi(index);
478 loop->appendNew<Value>(
479 proc, Branch, Origin(),
480 loop->appendNew<Value>(
481 proc, LessThan, Origin(), nextIndex,
482 loop->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 100)));
483 loop->setSuccessors(loop, end);
484
485 end->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin());
486}

488static std::array<int, 100> makeArrayForLoops()
489{
490 std::array<int, 100> result;
491 for (unsigned i = 0; i < result.size(); ++i)
492 result[i] = i & 1;
493 return result;
494}

496template<typename Func>
497void generateLoopNotBackwardsDominant(Procedure& proc, std::array<int, 100>& array, const Func& func)
498{
499 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
500 BasicBlock* loopHeader = proc.addBlock();
501 BasicBlock* loopCall = proc.addBlock();
502 BasicBlock* loopFooter = proc.addBlock();
503 BasicBlock* end = proc.addBlock();
504
505 UpsilonValue* initialIndex = root->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(
506 proc, Origin(), root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 0));
507 // If you look carefully, you'll notice that this is an extremely sneaky use of Upsilon that demonstrates
508 // the extent to which our SSA is different from normal-person SSA.
509 UpsilonValue* defaultOne = root->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(
510 proc, Origin(), root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 1));
511 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Jump, Origin());
512 root->setSuccessors(loopHeader);
513
514 Value* index = loopHeader->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Int32, Origin());
515 initialIndex->setPhi(index);
516
517 // if (array[index])
518 loopHeader->appendNew<Value>(
519 proc, Branch, Origin(),
520 loopHeader->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
521 proc, Load, Int32, Origin(),
522 loopHeader->appendNew<Value>(
523 proc, Add, Origin(),
524 loopHeader->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), &array),
525 loopHeader->appendNew<Value>(
526 proc, Mul, Origin(),
527 loopHeader->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZExt32, Origin(), index),
528 loopHeader->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), sizeof(int))))));
529 loopHeader->setSuccessors(loopCall, loopFooter);
530
531 Value* functionCall = func(loopCall, index);
532 UpsilonValue* oneFromFunction = loopCall->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), functionCall);
533 loopCall->appendNew<Value>(proc, Jump, Origin());
534 loopCall->setSuccessors(loopFooter);
535
536 Value* one = loopFooter->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Int32, Origin());
537 defaultOne->setPhi(one);
538 oneFromFunction->setPhi(one);
539 Value* nextIndex = loopFooter->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), index, one);
540 UpsilonValue* loopIndex = loopFooter->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), nextIndex);
541 loopIndex->setPhi(index);
542 loopFooter->appendNew<Value>(
543 proc, Branch, Origin(),
544 loopFooter->appendNew<Value>(
545 proc, LessThan, Origin(), nextIndex,
546 loopFooter->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 100)));
547 loopFooter->setSuccessors(loopHeader, end);
548
549 end->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin());
550}

552static JSC_DECLARE_JIT_OPERATION_WITHOUT_WTF_INTERNAL(oneFunction, int, (int* callCount));
553JSC_DEFINE_JIT_OPERATION(oneFunction, int, (int* callCount))
554{
555 (*callCount)++;
556 return 1;
557}

559static JSC_DECLARE_JIT_OPERATION_WITHOUT_WTF_INTERNAL(noOpFunction, void, ());
560JSC_DEFINE_JIT_OPERATION(noOpFunction, void, ())
561{
562}

564void testLICMPure()
565{
566 Procedure proc;
567
568 if (proc.optLevel() < 2)
569 return;
570
571 generateLoop(
572 proc,
573 [&] (BasicBlock* loop, Value*) -> Value* {
574 return loop->appendNew<CCallValue>(
575 proc, Int32, Origin(), Effects::none(),
576 loop->appendNew<ConstPtrValue>(proc, Origin(), tagCFunction<OperationPtrTag>(oneFunction)),
577 loop->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
578 });
579
580 unsigned callCount = 0;
581 compileAndRun<void>(proc, &callCount);
582 CHECK_EQ(callCount, 1u);
583}

1037void testDepend32()
1038{
1039 Procedure proc;
1040 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1041 Value* ptr = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
1042 Value* first = root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(proc, Load, Int32, Origin(), ptr, 0);
1043 Value* second = root->appendNew<MemoryValue>(
1044 proc, Load, Int32, Origin(),
1045 root->appendNew<Value>(
1046 proc, Add, Origin(), ptr,
1047 root->appendNew<Value>(
1048 proc, ZExt32, Origin(),
1049 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Depend, Origin(), first))),
1050 4);
1051 root->appendNew<Value>(
1052 proc, Return, Origin(),
1053 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), first, second));
1054
1055 int32_t values[2];
1056 values[0] = 42;
1057 values[1] = 0xbeef;
1058
1059 auto code = compileProc(proc);
1060 if (isARM64())
1061 checkUsesInstruction(*code, "eor");
1062 else if (isX86()) {
1063 checkDoesNotUseInstruction(*code, "mfence");
1064 checkDoesNotUseInstruction(*code, "lock");
1065 }
1066 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int32_t>(*code, values), 42 + 0xbeef);
1067}

1099void testWasmBoundsCheck(unsigned offset)
1100{
1101 Procedure proc;
1102 if (proc.optLevel() < 1)
1103 return;
1104 GPRReg pinned = GPRInfo::argumentGPR1;
1105 proc.pinRegister(pinned);
1106
1107 proc.setWasmBoundsCheckGenerator([=] (CCallHelpers& jit, GPRReg pinnedGPR) {
1108 CHECK_EQ(pinnedGPR, pinned);
1109
1110 // This should always work because a function this simple should never have callee
1111 // saves.
1112 jit.move(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(42), GPRInfo::returnValueGPR);
1113 jit.emitFunctionEpilogue();
1114 jit.ret();
1115 });
1116
1117 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1118 Value* left = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
1119 if (pointerType() != Int32)
1120 left = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(), left);
1121 root->appendNew<WasmBoundsCheckValue>(proc, Origin(), pinned, left, offset);
1122 Value* result = root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 0x42);
1123 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result);
1124
1125 auto code = compileProc(proc);
1126 uint32_t bound = 2 + offset;
1127 auto computeResult = [&] (uint32_t input) {
1128 return input + offset < bound ? 0x42 : 42;
1129 };
1130
1131 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int32_t>(*code, 1, bound), computeResult(1));
1132 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int32_t>(*code, 3, bound), computeResult(3));
1133 CHECK_EQ(invoke<int32_t>(*code, 2, bound), computeResult(2));
1134}
1135
1136void testWasmAddress()
1137{
1138 Procedure proc;
1139 GPRReg pinnedGPR = GPRInfo::argumentGPR2;
1140 proc.pinRegister(pinnedGPR);
1141
1142 unsigned loopCount = 100;
1143 Vector<unsigned> values(loopCount);
1144 unsigned numToStore = 42;
1145
1146 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1147 BasicBlock* header = proc.addBlock();
1148 BasicBlock* body = proc.addBlock();
1149 BasicBlock* continuation = proc.addBlock();
1150
1151 // Root
1152 Value* loopCountValue = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(), root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0));
1153 Value* valueToStore = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Trunc, Origin(), root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1));
1154 UpsilonValue* beginUpsilon = root->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(), root->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 0));
1155 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), header);
1156
1157 // Header
1158 Value* indexPhi = header->appendNew<Value>(proc, Phi, Int32, Origin());
1159 header->appendNewControlValue(proc, Branch, Origin(),
1160 header->appendNew<Value>(proc, Below, Origin(), indexPhi, loopCountValue),
1161 body, continuation);
1162
1163 // Body
1164 Value* pointer = body->appendNew<Value>(proc, Mul, Origin(), indexPhi,
1165 body->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), sizeof(unsigned)));
1166 pointer = body->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZExt32, Origin(), pointer);
1167 body->appendNew<MemoryValue>(proc, Store, Origin(), valueToStore,
1168 body->appendNew<WasmAddressValue>(proc, Origin(), pointer, pinnedGPR), 0);
1169 UpsilonValue* incUpsilon = body->appendNew<UpsilonValue>(proc, Origin(),
1170 body->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), indexPhi,
1171 body->appendNew<Const32Value>(proc, Origin(), 1)));
1172 body->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), header);
1173
1174 // Continuation
1175 continuation->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin());
1176
1177 beginUpsilon->setPhi(indexPhi);
1178 incUpsilon->setPhi(indexPhi);
1179
1180
1181 auto code = compileProc(proc);
1182 invoke<void>(*code, loopCount, numToStore, values.data());
1183 for (unsigned value : values)
1184 CHECK_EQ(numToStore, value);
1185}

1233static NEVER_INLINE bool doubleEq(double a, double b) { return a == b; }
1234static NEVER_INLINE bool doubleNeq(double a, double b) { return a != b; }
1235static NEVER_INLINE bool doubleGt(double a, double b) { return a > b; }
1236static NEVER_INLINE bool doubleGte(double a, double b) { return a >= b; }
1237static NEVER_INLINE bool doubleLt(double a, double b) { return a < b; }
1238static NEVER_INLINE bool doubleLte(double a, double b) { return a <= b; }
1239
1240void testDoubleLiteralComparison(double a, double b)
1241{
1242 using Test = std::tuple<B3::Opcode, bool (*)(double, double)>;
1243 StdList<Test> tests = {
1244 Test { NotEqual, doubleNeq },
1245 Test { Equal, doubleEq },
1246 Test { EqualOrUnordered, doubleEq },
1247 Test { GreaterThan, doubleGt },
1248 Test { GreaterEqual, doubleGte },
1249 Test { LessThan, doubleLt },
1250 Test { LessEqual, doubleLte },
1251 };
1252
1253 for (const Test& test : tests) {
1254 Procedure proc;
1255 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1256 Value* valueA = root->appendNew<ConstDoubleValue>(proc, Origin(), a);
1257 Value* valueB = root->appendNew<ConstDoubleValue>(proc, Origin(), b);
1258
1259 // This is here just to make reduceDoubleToFloat do things.
1260 Value* valueC = root->appendNew<ConstDoubleValue>(proc, Origin(), 0.0);
1261 Value* valueAsFloat = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(), valueC);
1262
1263 root->appendNewControlValue(
1264 proc, Return, Origin(),
1265 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, BitAnd, Origin(),
1266 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, std::get<0>(test), Origin(), valueA, valueB),
1267 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, Equal, Origin(), valueAsFloat, valueAsFloat)));
1268
1269 CHECK(!!compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc) == std::get<1>(test)(a, b));
1270 }
1271}
1272
1273void testFloatEqualOrUnorderedFolding()
1274{
1275 for (auto& first : floatingPointOperands<float>()) {
1276 for (auto& second : floatingPointOperands<float>()) {
1277 float a = first.value;
1278 float b = second.value;
1279 bool expectedResult = (a == b) || std::isunordered(a, b);
1280 Procedure proc;
1281 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1282 Value* constA = root->appendNew<ConstFloatValue>(proc, Origin(), a);
1283 Value* constB = root->appendNew<ConstFloatValue>(proc, Origin(), b);
1284
1285 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(),
1286 root->appendNew<Value>(
1287 proc, EqualOrUnordered, Origin(),
1288 constA,
1289 constB));
1290 CHECK(!!compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc) == expectedResult);
1291 }
1292 }
1293}
1294
1295void testFloatEqualOrUnorderedFoldingNaN()
1296{
1297 StdList<float> nans = {
1298 bitwise_cast<float>(0xfffffffd),
1299 bitwise_cast<float>(0xfffffffe),
1300 bitwise_cast<float>(0xfffffff0),
1301 static_cast<float>(PNaN),
1302 };
1303
1304 unsigned i = 0;
1305 for (float nan : nans) {
1306 RELEASE_ASSERT(std::isnan(nan));
1307 Procedure proc;
1308 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1309 Value* a = root->appendNew<ConstFloatValue>(proc, Origin(), nan);
1310 Value* b = root->appendNew<Value>(proc, DoubleToFloat, Origin(),
1311 root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0));
1312
1313 if (i % 2)
1314 std::swap(a, b);
1315 ++i;
1316 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(),
1317 root->appendNew<Value>(proc, EqualOrUnordered, Origin(), a, b));
1318 CHECK(!!compileAndRun<int32_t>(proc, static_cast<double>(1.0)));
1319 }
1320}

1357

1359 regs.exclude(RegisterSet::stackRegisters());
1360 regs.exclude(RegisterSet::reservedHardwareRegisters());
1361 regs.exclude(RegisterSet::calleeSaveRegisters());
1362 regs.exclude(RegisterSet::argumentGPRS());

1367 ++i;

1390 ptr->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());

1392 ptr->appendSomeRegister(arg1);
1393 ptr->setGenerator(

1395 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
1396 jit.move(params[1].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
1397 });
1398
1399 Value* condition = root->appendNew<Value>(
1400 proc, Equal, Origin(),
1401 ptr,
1402 root->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), 0));
1403

1405 proc, Branch, Origin(),
1406 condition,
1407 FrequentedBlock(likely, FrequencyClass::Normal), FrequentedBlock(unlikely, FrequencyClass::Rare));

1510void testInfiniteLoopDoesntCauseBadHoisting()
1511{
1512 Procedure proc;
1513 if (proc.optLevel() < 2)
1514 return;
1515 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1516 BasicBlock* header = proc.addBlock();
1517 BasicBlock* loadBlock = proc.addBlock();
1518 BasicBlock* postLoadBlock = proc.addBlock();
1519
1520 Value* arg = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
1521 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), header);
1522
1523 header->appendNewControlValue(
1524 proc, Branch, Origin(),
1525 header->appendNew<Value>(proc, Equal, Origin(),
1526 arg,
1527 header->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), 10)), header, loadBlock);
1528
1529 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = loadBlock->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, Void, Origin());
1530 patchpoint->effects = Effects::none();
1531 patchpoint->effects.writesLocalState = true; // Don't DCE this.
1532 patchpoint->setGenerator(
1533 [&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams&) {
1534 // This works because we don't have callee saves.
1535 jit.emitFunctionEpilogue();
1536 jit.ret();
1537 });
1538
1539 Value* badLoad = loadBlock->appendNew<MemoryValue>(proc, Load, Int64, Origin(), arg, 0);
1540
1541 loadBlock->appendNewControlValue(
1542 proc, Branch, Origin(),
1543 loadBlock->appendNew<Value>(proc, Equal, Origin(),
1544 badLoad,
1545 loadBlock->appendNew<Const64Value>(proc, Origin(), 45)), header, postLoadBlock);
1546
1547 postLoadBlock->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), badLoad);
1548
1549 // The patchpoint early ret() works because we don't have callee saves.
1550 auto code = compileProc(proc);
1551 RELEASE_ASSERT(!proc.calleeSaveRegisterAtOffsetList().size());
1552 invoke<void>(*code, static_cast<uint64_t>(55)); // Shouldn't crash dereferncing 55.
1553}

1668template<bool shouldFixSSA>
1669static void tailDupedTuplePair(unsigned first, double second)
1670{
1671 Procedure proc;
1672 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1673 BasicBlock* truthy = proc.addBlock();
1674 BasicBlock* falsey = proc.addBlock();
1675
1676 Type tupleType = proc.addTuple({ Int32, Double });
1677 Variable* var = proc.addVariable(tupleType);
1678
1679 Value* test = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
1680 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, tupleType, Origin());
1681 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
1682 patchpoint->resultConstraints = { ValueRep::SomeRegister, ValueRep::stackArgument(0) };
1683 patchpoint->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
1684 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
1685 jit.move(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(first), params[0].gpr());
1686 jit.store64(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm64(bitwise_cast<uint64_t>(second)), CCallHelpers::Address(CCallHelpers::framePointerRegister, params[1].offsetFromFP()));
1687 });
1688 root->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, Set, Origin(), var, patchpoint);
1689 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Branch, Origin(), test, FrequentedBlock(truthy), FrequentedBlock(falsey));
1690
1691 auto addDup = [&] (BasicBlock* block) {
1692 Value* tuple = block->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), var);
1693 Value* i32 = block->appendNew<Value>(proc, ZExt32, Origin(),
1694 block->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Int32, tuple, 0));
1695 i32 = block->appendNew<Value>(proc, IToD, Origin(), i32);
1696 Value* f64 = block->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Double, tuple, 1);
1697 block->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), block->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), i32, f64));
1698 };
1699
1700 addDup(truthy);
1701 addDup(falsey);
1702
1703 proc.resetReachability();
1704 if (shouldFixSSA)
1705 fixSSA(proc);
1706 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<double>(proc, first), first + second);
1707}

1709template<bool shouldFixSSA>
1710static void tuplePairVariableLoop(unsigned first, uint64_t second)
1711{
1712 Procedure proc;
1713 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1714 BasicBlock* body = proc.addBlock();
1715 BasicBlock* exit = proc.addBlock();
1716
1717 Type tupleType = proc.addTuple({ Int32, Int64 });
1718 Variable* var = proc.addVariable(tupleType);
1719
1720 {
1721 Value* first = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
1722 Value* second = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR1);
1723 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, tupleType, Origin());
1724 patchpoint->append({ first, ValueRep::SomeRegister });
1725 patchpoint->append({ second, ValueRep::SomeRegister });
1726 patchpoint->resultConstraints = { ValueRep::SomeEarlyRegister, ValueRep::SomeEarlyRegister };
1727 patchpoint->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
1728 jit.move(params[2].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
1729 jit.move(params[3].gpr(), params[1].gpr());
1730 });
1731 root->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, Set, Origin(), var, patchpoint);
1732 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), body);
1733 }
1734
1735 {
1736 Value* tuple = body->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), var);
1737 Value* first = body->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Int32, tuple, 0);
1738 Value* second = body->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Int64, tuple, 1);
1739 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = body->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, tupleType, Origin());
1740 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
1741 patchpoint->append({ first, ValueRep::SomeRegister });
1742 patchpoint->append({ second, ValueRep::SomeRegister });
1743 patchpoint->resultConstraints = { ValueRep::SomeEarlyRegister, ValueRep::stackArgument(0) };
1744 patchpoint->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
1745 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
1746 CHECK(params[3].gpr() != params[0].gpr());
1747 CHECK(params[2].gpr() != params[0].gpr());
1748 jit.add64(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(1), params[3].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
1749 jit.store64(params[0].gpr(), CCallHelpers::Address(CCallHelpers::framePointerRegister, params[1].offsetFromFP()));
1750
1751 jit.move(params[2].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
1752 jit.urshift32(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(1), params[0].gpr());
1753 });
1754 body->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, Set, Origin(), var, patchpoint);
1755 Value* condition = body->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Int32, patchpoint, 0);
1756 body->appendNewControlValue(proc, Branch, Origin(), condition, FrequentedBlock(body), FrequentedBlock(exit));
1757 }
1758
1759 {
1760 Value* tuple = exit->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), var);
1761 Value* second = exit->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Int64, tuple, 1);
1762 exit->appendNew<Value>(proc, Return, Origin(), second);
1763 }
1764
1765 proc.resetReachability();
1766 validate(proc);
1767 if (shouldFixSSA)
1768 fixSSA(proc);
1769 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<uint64_t>(proc, first, second), second + (first ? getMSBSet(first) : first) + 1);
1770}

1772template<bool shouldFixSSA>
1773static void tupleNestedLoop(int32_t first, double second)
1774{
1775 Procedure proc;
1776 BasicBlock* root = proc.addBlock();
1777 BasicBlock* outerLoop = proc.addBlock();
1778 BasicBlock* innerLoop = proc.addBlock();
1779 BasicBlock* outerContinuation = proc.addBlock();
1780
1781 Type tupleType = proc.addTuple({ Int32, Double, Int32 });
1782 Variable* varOuter = proc.addVariable(tupleType);
1783 Variable* varInner = proc.addVariable(tupleType);
1784 Variable* tookInner = proc.addVariable(Int32);
1785
1786 {
1787 Value* first = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), GPRInfo::argumentGPR0);
1788 Value* second = root->appendNew<ArgumentRegValue>(proc, Origin(), FPRInfo::argumentFPR0);
1789 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = root->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, tupleType, Origin());
1790 patchpoint->append({ first, ValueRep::SomeRegisterWithClobber });
1791 patchpoint->append({ second, ValueRep::SomeRegisterWithClobber });
1792 patchpoint->resultConstraints = { ValueRep::SomeRegister, ValueRep::SomeRegister, ValueRep::SomeEarlyRegister };
1793 patchpoint->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
1794 jit.move(params[3].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
1795 jit.move(params[0].gpr(), params[2].gpr());
1796 jit.move(params[4].fpr(), params[1].fpr());
1797 });
1798 root->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, Set, Origin(), varOuter, patchpoint);
1799 root->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, Set, Origin(), tookInner, root->appendIntConstant(proc, Origin(), Int32, 0));
1800 root->appendNewControlValue(proc, Jump, Origin(), outerLoop);
1801 }
1802
1803 {
1804 Value* tuple = outerLoop->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), varOuter);
1805 Value* first = outerLoop->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Int32, tuple, 0);
1806 Value* second = outerLoop->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Double, tuple, 1);
1807 Value* third = outerLoop->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), tookInner);
1808 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = outerLoop->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, tupleType, Origin());
1809 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
1810 patchpoint->append({ first, ValueRep::SomeRegisterWithClobber });
1811 patchpoint->append({ second, ValueRep::SomeRegisterWithClobber });
1812 patchpoint->append({ third, ValueRep::SomeRegisterWithClobber });
1813 patchpoint->resultConstraints = { ValueRep::SomeRegister, ValueRep::SomeRegister, ValueRep::SomeRegister };
1814 patchpoint->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
1815 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
1816 jit.move(params[3].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
1817 jit.moveConditionally32(CCallHelpers::Equal, params[5].gpr(), CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(0), params[0].gpr(), params[5].gpr(), params[2].gpr());
1818 jit.move(params[4].fpr(), params[1].fpr());
1819 });
1820 outerLoop->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, Set, Origin(), varOuter, patchpoint);
1821 outerLoop->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, Set, Origin(), varInner, patchpoint);
1822 Value* condition = outerLoop->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Int32, patchpoint, 2);
1823 outerLoop->appendNewControlValue(proc, Branch, Origin(), condition, FrequentedBlock(outerContinuation), FrequentedBlock(innerLoop));
1824 }
1825
1826 {
1827 Value* tuple = innerLoop->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), varInner);
1828 Value* first = innerLoop->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Int32, tuple, 0);
1829 Value* second = innerLoop->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Double, tuple, 1);
1830 PatchpointValue* patchpoint = innerLoop->appendNew<PatchpointValue>(proc, tupleType, Origin());
1831 patchpoint->clobber(RegisterSet::macroScratchRegisters());
1832 patchpoint->append({ first, ValueRep::SomeRegisterWithClobber });
1833 patchpoint->append({ second, ValueRep::SomeRegisterWithClobber });
1834 patchpoint->resultConstraints = { ValueRep::SomeRegister, ValueRep::SomeRegister, ValueRep::SomeEarlyRegister };
1835 patchpoint->setGenerator([&] (CCallHelpers& jit, const StackmapGenerationParams& params) {
1836 AllowMacroScratchRegisterUsage allowScratch(jit);
1837 jit.move(params[3].gpr(), params[0].gpr());
1838 jit.move(CCallHelpers::TrustedImm32(0), params[2].gpr());
1839 jit.move(params[4].fpr(), params[1].fpr());
1840 });
1841 innerLoop->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, Set, Origin(), varOuter, patchpoint);
1842 innerLoop->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, Set, Origin(), varInner, patchpoint);
1843 Value* condition = innerLoop->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Int32, patchpoint, 2);
1844 innerLoop->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, Set, Origin(), tookInner, innerLoop->appendIntConstant(proc, Origin(), Int32, 1));
1845 innerLoop->appendNewControlValue(proc, Branch, Origin(), condition, FrequentedBlock(innerLoop), FrequentedBlock(outerLoop));
1846 }
1847
1848 {
1849 Value* tuple = outerContinuation->appendNew<VariableValue>(proc, B3::Get, Origin(), varInner);
1850 Value* first = outerContinuation->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Int32, tuple, 0);
1851 Value* second = outerContinuation->appendNew<ExtractValue>(proc, Origin(), Double, tuple, 1);
1852 Value* result = outerContinuation->appendNew<Value>(proc, Add, Origin(), second, outerContinuation->appendNew<Value>(proc, IToD, Origin(), first));
1853 outerContinuation->appendNewControlValue(proc, Return, Origin(), result);
1854 }
1855
1856 proc.resetReachability();
1857 validate(proc);
1858 if (shouldFixSSA)
1859 fixSSA(proc);
1860 CHECK_EQ(compileAndRun<double>(proc, first, second), first + second);
1861}
